Program: Outlook
Title: Foster Father to the Most Vulnerable
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04w19kh
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 15 Mar 2017
Mohamed Bzeek from Los Angeles has dedicated his life to fostering terminally ill children. Prince Louis Albert De Broglie owns Deyrolle, the famous taxidermy shop, in Paris. Jose Arrieta from Venezuela is part of Project Alcatraz, an initiative to turn young men away from gangs. Floyd Norman joined Disney in 1956 and was the company's first African American animator. Image: Mohamed Bzeek Show less